main event: A bright, silvery object was observed moving slowly with a rocking motion in the sky over Portland, Oregon on June 23, 1967.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 50-60 feet in diameter.
The object was observed flashing red, white, and blue colors.
The object appeared to be hovering over something or waiting for something to materialize.
The witness could not determine what the object was, but stated it was not any known aircraft or satellite.
Additional similar objects had been reported in the area.
